# ─── Secrets — never commit ───
.env
.env.*
*.env

# ─── Python bytecode / build junk ───
__pycache__/
*.py[cod]
*$py.class

# ─── OS / editor cruft ───
.DS_Store
Thumbs.db
desktop.ini

# ─── Microsoft Office lock/owner temp files (created while a doc is open) ───
~$*.docx
~$*.xlsx
~$*.pptx

# ─── Virtualenvs & tool caches ───
.venv/
venv/
env/
.pytest_cache/
.mypy_cache/
.ruff_cache/
.ipynb_checkpoints/

# ─── Built workbook deliverables — regenerable, not committed ───
# Every .xlsx in this tree is emitted by a build_*.py run (the combined DDG-51
# deliverable, the standalone TAM/SAM QA builds, and the SAM master reconstruction).
# The pipeline source + the extracted/*.csv inputs ARE tracked, so any output
# rebuilds from a clean clone. The factory reads only CSVs — no .xlsx is a build
# input — so ignoring them all is safe. Mirrors ooxml_build_pipelines_light's
# convention of tracking the reproducible pipeline; here we additionally drop the
# large binary it emits.
*.xlsx

# Exception: external commercial-registry source artifacts (S&P Global / IHS
# Sea-web MIRS extract) are cited by the hull-milestone provenance and are NOT
# build outputs, so they are tracked as source-of-record evidence.
!ddg/data/workbook_inputs/reference/*.xlsx
